subject: p16435402
History: Recent cough and adventitial breath sounds in the right lower lobe.
Findings: PA and lateral radiographs of the chest demonstrate clear lungs. There are bilateral nipple shadows overlying the lower lung fields, which should not be confused with an intrapulmonary process. There is no pneumothorax or pleural effusion. The hila and cardiomediastinal contours are normal. Pulmonary vascularity is normal. Callus formation around the posterior left eighth rib is consistent with remote history of fracture. Cholecystectomy clips can once again be seen in the right upper quadrant of the abdomen.
